Graphite.name: graphite
Graphite.description: Used in electrical components and turret ammunition.

Silicon.name: silicon
Silicon.description: Used in solar panels, complex electronics and homing turret ammunition.

Plastanium.name: plastanium
Plastanium.description: Used in advanced units, insulation and fragmentation ammunition.

Phase Fabric.name: phase-fabric
Phase Fabric.description: Used in advanced electronics and self-repairing structures.

Surge Alloy.name: surge-alloy
Surge Alloy.description: Used in advanced weaponry and reactive defense structures.

Spore Pod.name: spore-pod
Spore Pod.details: Spores. Likely a synthetic life form. Emit gases toxic to other biological life. Extremely invasive. Highly flammable in certain conditions.
Spore Pod.description: Used for conversion into oil, explosives and fuel.

Blast Compound.name: blast-compound
Blast Compound.description: Used in bombs and explosive ammunition.

Pyratite.name: pyratite
Pyratite.description: Used in incendiary weapons and combustion-fueled generators.

Water.name: water
Water.description: Used for cooling machines and waste processing.

Slag.name: slag
Slag.description: Refined in separators into constituent metals, or sprayed at enemies as a weapon.

Multi-Press.name: multi-press
Multi-Press.description: Compresses coal into graphite. Requires water as coolant.

Silicon Smelter.name: silicon-smelter
Silicon Smelter.description: Refines silicon from sand and coal.

Silicon Crucible.name: silicon-crucible
Silicon Crucible.description: Refines silicon from sand and coal, using pyratite as an additional heat source. More efficient in hot locations.

Kiln.name: kiln
Kiln.description: Smelts sand and lead into metaglass.

Plastanium Compressor.name: plastanium-compressor
Plastanium Compressor.description: Produces plastanium from oil and titanium.

Phase Weaver.name: phase-weaver
Phase Weaver.description: Synthesizes phase fabric from thorium and sand.

Alloy Smelter.name: alloy-smelter
Alloy Smelter.description: Fuses titanium, lead, silicon and copper into surge alloy.

Cryofluid Mixer.name: cryofluid-mixer
Cryofluid Mixer.description: Mixes water and fine titanium powder to produce cryofluid.

Pyratite Mixer.name: pyratite-mixer
Pyratite Mixer.description: Mixes coal, lead and sand into pyratite.

Blast Mixer.name: blast-mixer
Blast Mixer.description: Produces blast compound from pyratite and spore pods.

Separator.name: separator
Separator.description: Separates slag into its mineral components.

Disassembler.name: disassembler
Disassembler.description: Separates slag into trace amounts of exotic mineral components at low efficiency. Can produce thorium.

Incinerator.name: incinerator
Incinerator.description: Vaporizes any item or liquid it receives.

Plastanium Wall.name: plastanium-wall
Plastanium Wall.description: Protects structures from enemy projectiles. Absorbs lasers and electric arcs. Blocks automatic power connections.

Large Plastanium Wall.name: plastanium-wall-large
Large Plastanium Wall.description: Protects structures from enemy projectiles. Absorbs lasers and electric arcs. Blocks automatic power connections.

Phase Wall.name: phase-wall
Phase Wall.description: Protects structures from enemy projectiles, reflecting most bullets upon impact.

Large Phase Wall.name: phase-wall-large
Large Phase Wall.description: Protects structures from enemy projectiles, reflecting most bullets upon impact.

Surge Wall.name: surge-wall
Surge Wall.description: Protects structures from enemy projectiles, periodically releasing electric arcs upon contact.

Large Surge Wall.name: surge-wall-large
Large Surge Wall.description: Protects structures from enemy projectiles, periodically releasing electric arcs upon contact.

Door.name: door
Door.description: A wall that can be opened and closed.

Large Door.name: door-large
Large Door.description: A wall that can be opened and closed.

Mender.name: mender
Mender.description:
Periodically repairs blocks in its vicinity.
Optionally uses silicon to boost range and efficiency.

Mend Projector.name: mend-projector
Mend Projector.description:
Repairs blocks in its vicinity.
Optionally uses phase fabric to boost range and efficiency.

Overdrive Projector.name: overdrive-projector
Overdrive Projector.description:
Increases the speed of nearby buildings.
Optionally uses phase fabric to boost range and efficiency.

Overdrive Dome.name: overdrive-dome
Overdrive Dome.description: Increases the speed of nearby buildings. Requires phase fabric and silicon to operate.

Force Projector.name: force-projector
Force Projector.description:
Creates a hexagonal force field around itself, protecting buildings and units inside from damage.
Overheats if too much damage is sustained. Optionally uses coolant to prevent overheating. Phase fabric increases shield size.

Shock Mine.name: shock-mine
Shock Mine.description: Releases electric arcs upon enemy unit contact.

Titanium Conveyor.name: titanium-conveyor
Titanium Conveyor.description: Transports items forward. Faster than a standard conveyor.

Plastanium Conveyor.name: plastanium-conveyor
Plastanium Conveyor.description: Transports items forward in batches. Accepts items at the back, and unloads them in three directions at the front. Requires multiple loading and unloading points for peak throughput.

Armored Conveyor.name: armored-conveyor
Armored Conveyor.description: Moves items forward. Does not accept inputs from the sides.

Junction.name: junction
Junction.description: Acts as a bridge for two crossing conveyor belts.

Bridge Conveyor.name: bridge-conveyor
Bridge Conveyor.description: Transports items over terrain or buildings.

Phase Conveyor.name: phase-conveyor
Phase Conveyor.description: Instantly transports items over terrain or buildings. Longer range than the item bridge, but requires power.

Sorter.name: sorter
Sorter.description: If an input item matches the selection, it passes forward. Otherwise, the item is outputted to the left and right.

Inverted Sorter.name: inverted-sorter
Inverted Sorter.description: Similar to a standard sorter, but outputs selected items to the sides instead.

Router.name: router
Router.details: A necessary evil. Using next to production inputs is not advised, as they will get clogged by output.
Router.description: Distributes input items to 3 output directions equally.

Distributor.name: distributor
Distributor.description: Distributes input items to 7 output directions equally.

Overflow Gate.name: overflow-gate
Overflow Gate.description: Only outputs items to the left and right if the front path is blocked.

Underflow Gate.name: underflow-gate
Underflow Gate.description: Opposite of an overflow gate. Outputs to the front if the left and right paths are blocked.

Mass Driver.name: mass-driver
Mass Driver.description: Long-range item transport structure. Collects batches of items and shoots them to other mass drivers.

Mechanical Pump.name: mechanical-pump
Mechanical Pump.description: Pumps and outputs liquids. Does not require power.

Rotary Pump.name: rotary-pump
Rotary Pump.description: Pumps and outputs liquids. Requires power.

Conduit.name: conduit
Conduit.description: Moves liquids forward. Used in conjunction with pumps and other conduits.

Pulse Conduit.name: pulse-conduit
Pulse Conduit.description: Moves liquids forward. Transports faster and stores more than standard conduits.

Plated Conduit.name: plated-conduit
Plated Conduit.description: Moves liquids forward. Does not accept input from the sides. Does not leak.

Liquid Router.name: liquid-router
Liquid Router.description: Accepts liquids from one direction and outputs them to up to 3 other directions equally. Can also store a certain amount of liquid.

Liquid Tank.name: liquid-tank
Liquid Tank.description: Stores a large amount of liquid. Outputs to all sides, similarly to a liquid router.

Liquid Junction.name: liquid-junction
Liquid Junction.description: Acts as a bridge for two crossing conduits.

Bridge Conduit.name: bridge-conduit
Bridge Conduit.description: Transports liquids over terrain or buildings.

Phase Conduit.name: phase-conduit
Phase Conduit.description: Transports liquids over terrain or buildings. Longer range than the bridge conduit, but requires power.

Power Node.name: power-node
Power Node.description: Transmits power to connected nodes. The node will receive power from or supply power to any adjacent blocks.

Large Power Node.name: power-node-large
Large Power Node.description: An advanced power node with greater range.

Surge Tower.name: surge-tower
Surge Tower.description: A long-range power node with fewer available connections.

Battery Diode.name: diode
Battery Diode.description: Moves battery power in one direction, but only if the other side has less power stored.

Battery.name: battery
Battery.description: Stores power in times of surplus energy. Outputs power in times of deficit.

Large Battery.name: battery-large
Large Battery.description: Stores power in times of surplus energy. Outputs power in times of deficit. Higher capacity than a regular battery.

Combustion Generator.name: combustion-generator
Combustion Generator.description: Generates power by burning flammable materials, such as coal.

Thermal Generator.name: thermal-generator
Thermal Generator.description: Generates power when placed in hot locations.

Steam Generator.name: steam-generator
Steam Generator.description: Generates power by burning flammable materials and converting water to steam.

Differential Generator.name: differential-generator
Differential Generator.description: Generates large amounts of energy. Utilizes the temperature difference between cryofluid and burning pyratite.

RTG Generator.name: rtg-generator
RTG Generator.description: Uses the heat of decaying radioactive compounds to produce energy at a slow rate.

Solar Panel.name: solar-panel
Solar Panel.description: Provides a small amount of power from the sun.

Large Solar Panel.name: solar-panel-large
Large Solar Panel.description: Provides a small amount of power from the sun. More efficient than the standard solar panel.

Thorium Reactor.name: thorium-reactor
Thorium Reactor.description: Generates significant amounts of power from thorium. Requires constant cooling. Will explode violently if insufficient amounts of coolant are supplied.

Impact Reactor.name: impact-reactor
Impact Reactor.description: Creates massive amounts of power at peak efficiency. Requires a significant power input to kickstart the process.

Mechanical Drill.name: mechanical-drill
Mechanical Drill.description: When placed on ore, outputs items at a slow pace indefinitely. Only capable of mining basic resources.

Pneumatic Drill.name: pneumatic-drill
Pneumatic Drill.description: An improved drill, capable of mining titanium. Mines at a faster pace than a mechanical drill.

Laser Drill.name: laser-drill
Laser Drill.description: Allows drilling even faster through laser technology, but requires power. Capable of mining thorium.

Airblast Drill.name: blast-drill
Airblast Drill.description: The ultimate drill. Requires large amounts of power.

Water Extractor.name: water-extractor
Water Extractor.description: Extracts groundwater. Used in locations with no surface water available.

Cultivator.name: cultivator
Cultivator.details: Recovered technology. Used to produce massive amounts of biomass as efficiently as possible. Likely the initial incubator of the spores now covering Serpulo.
Cultivator.description: Cultivates tiny concentrations of atmospheric spores into spore pods.

Oil Extractor.name: oil-extractor
Oil Extractor.description: Uses large amounts of power, sand and water to drill for oil.

Core: Shard.name: core-shard
Core: Shard.details: The first iteration. Compact. Self-replicating. Equipped with single-use launch thrusters. Not designed for interplanetary travel.
Core: Shard.description: Core of the base. Once destroyed, the sector is lost.

Core: Foundation.name: core-foundation
Core: Foundation.description: Core of the base. Well armored. Stores more resources than a Shard.

Core: Nucleus.name: core-nucleus
Core: Nucleus.description: Core of the base. Extremely well armored. Stores massive amounts of resources.

Vault.name: vault
Vault.description: Stores a large amount of items of each type. Contents can be retrieved with an unloader.

Container.name: container
Container.description: Stores a small amount of items of each type. Contents can be retrieved with an unloader.

Unloader.name: unloader
Unloader.description: Unloads the selected item from nearby blocks.

Scatter.name: scatter
Scatter.description: Fires clumps of lead, scrap or metaglass flak at enemy aircraft.

Scorch.name: scorch
Scorch.description: Burns any ground enemies close to it. Highly effective at close range.

Hail.name: hail
Hail.description: Fires small shells at ground enemies over long distances.

Wave.name: wave
Wave.description: Fires streams of liquid at enemies. Automatically extinguishes fires when supplied with water.

Lancer.name: lancer
Lancer.description: Charges and fires powerful beams of energy at ground targets.

Arc.name: arc
Arc.description: Fires arcs of electricity at ground targets.

Parallax.name: parallax
Parallax.description: Fires a tractor beam that pulls in air targets, damaging them in the process.

Salvo.name: salvo
Salvo.description: Fires quick salvos of bullets at enemies.

Segment.name: segment
Segment.description: Damages and destroys incoming projectiles. Laser projectiles are not targeted.

Tsunami.name: tsunami
Tsunami.description: Fires powerful streams of liquid at enemies. Automatically extinguishes fires when supplied with water.

Fuse.name: fuse
Fuse.description: Fires three close-range piercing blasts at nearby enemies.

Ripple.name: ripple
Ripple.description: Shoots clusters of shells at ground enemies over long distances.

Cyclone.name: cyclone
Cyclone.description: Fires explosive clumps of flak at nearby enemies.

Foreshadow.name: foreshadow
Foreshadow.description: Fires a large single-target bolt over long distances. Prioritizes enemies with higher max health.

Spectre.name: spectre
Spectre.description: Fires large armor-piercing bullets at air and ground targets.

Meltdown.name: meltdown
Meltdown.description: Charges and fires a persistent laser beam at nearby enemies. Requires coolant to operate.

Command Center.name: command-center
Command Center.description: Controls unit behavior with several different commands.

Ground Factory.name: ground-factory
Ground Factory.description: Produces ground units. Output units can be used directly, or moved into reconstructors for upgrading.

Air Factory.name: air-factory
Air Factory.description: Produces air units. Output units can be used directly, or moved into reconstructors for upgrading.

Naval Factory.name: naval-factory
Naval Factory.description: Produces naval units. Output units can be used directly, or moved into reconstructors for upgrading.

Additive Reconstructor.name: additive-reconstructor
Additive Reconstructor.description: Upgrades inputted units to the second tier.

Multiplicative Reconstructor.name: multiplicative-reconstructor
Multiplicative Reconstructor.description: Upgrades inputted units to the third tier.

Exponential Reconstructor.name: exponential-reconstructor
Exponential Reconstructor.description: Upgrades inputted units to the fourth tier.

Tetrative Reconstructor.name: tetrative-reconstructor
Tetrative Reconstructor.description: Upgrades inputted units to the fifth and final tier.

Repair Point.name: repair-point
Repair Point.description: Continuously repairs the closest damaged unit in its vicinity.

Repair Turret.name: repair-turret
Repair Turret.description: Continuously repairs the closest damaged unit in its vicinity. Optionally accepts coolant.

Payload Conveyor.name: payload-conveyor
Payload Conveyor.description: Moves large payloads, such as units from factories.

Payload Router.name: payload-router
Payload Router.description: Splits input payloads into 3 output directions.

Payload Propulsion Tower.name: payload-propulsion-tower
Payload Propulsion Tower.description: Long-range payload transport structure. Shoots payloads to other linked payload propulsion towers.

Power Void.name: power-void
Power Void.description: Voids all power inputted. Sandbox only.

Launch Pad.name: launch-pad
Launch Pad.description: Launches batches of items to selected sectors.

Interplanetary Accelerator.name: interplanetary-accelerator
Interplanetary Accelerator.description: A massive electromagnetic railgun tower. Accelerates cores to escape velocity for interplanetary deployment.

Message.name: message
Message.description: Stores a message for communication between allies.

Switch.name: switch
Switch.description: A toggleable switch. State can be read and controlled with logic processors.

Micro Processor.name: micro-processor
Micro Processor.description: Runs a sequence of logic instructions in a loop. Can be used to control units and buildings.

Logic Processor.name: logic-processor
Logic Processor.description: Runs a sequence of logic instructions in a loop. Can be used to control units and buildings. Faster than the micro processor.

Hyper Processor.name: hyper-processor
Hyper Processor.description: Runs a sequence of logic instructions in a loop. Can be used to control units and buildings. Faster than the logic processor.

Memory Cell.name: memory-cell
Memory Cell.description: Stores information for a logic processor.

Memory Bank.name: memory-bank
Memory Bank.description: Stores information for a logic processor. High capacity.

Logic Display.name: logic-display
Logic Display.description: Displays arbitrary graphics from a logic processor.

Large Logic Display.name: large-logic-display
Large Logic Display.description: Displays arbitrary graphics from a logic processor.

Oil.name: oil
Oil.description: Used in advanced material production and as incendiary ammunition.

Cryofluid.name: cryofluid
Cryofluid.description: Used as coolant in reactors, turrets and factories.
